#   CODE-014: mark: abc utf8/eq/suffix; collapse triplets

mark hand-rolls codepoint counting (= utf8CPLen), slice equality/prefix (= u8csEq/HasPrefix), and the '.mkd' suffix test (= u8csHasSuffix) with memcmp at several sites; close_para/list/quote and the inline B/I/D cases are structural triplets; and mark_refdef overlaps dog's MKDTRefDef. Route through abc and collapse the triplets.

##  Issues

abc utf8/eq/suffix helpers are hand-rolled; close/inline triplets; refdef overlap.

 -  mark_chars (MARK.c:37) = utf8CPLen; eq/prefix via memcmp at MARK.c:116, MARK.cli.c:150,156.
 -  '.mkd' suffix test (a_tail+memcmp) pasted 3x (MARK.c:130, MARK.cli.c:27,102) = u8csHasSuffix.
 -  close_para/list/quote (MARK.c:256,264,272) and B/I/D inline cases (MARK.c:186,191,196) are triplets.
 -  mark_refdef (MARK.c:69) overlaps dog MKDTRefDef (tok/MKDT.c:143).

##  Blockers

None; mark-internal except the refdef overlap with dog (reconcile, do not fork).

##  Planned

Swap the memcmp blocks for abc helpers; parameterize the triplets; reconcile refdef.

 -  Repro first (§17): mark render of a fixture .mkd stays byte-identical.
 -  utf8CPLen / u8csEq / u8csHasPrefix / u8csHasSuffix replace the memcmp blocks.
 -  One close(flag,tag) + one inline(tag) helper; refdef → reuse MKDTRefDef.

